	(text "TODO:\n* overvoltage protection (above 5.x V) on isolation side\n* overvoltage LED(s)? big RED; extra parts\n* run the CH341a directly from 5V! requires a capacitor\n	on V3 pin of .01µF-.1µF (not 472µF ...)\n	recalculate LED resistors\n	but is VBUS stable?\n* reset switch needed for sure in my experience; \n  better than disconnecting vbus\n\nDatasheet notes:\n* connect ACT to GND through 2KΩ to disable I²C EEPROM check\n   from datasheet: use as activity LED ... \n	connect LED from VCC to ACT through 1K resistor...\n	optional, usually omitted\n		but that procludes disabling EEPROM check!\n* capacitor from VCC to RST .1µF for reliable reset\n	in case of big C on VBUS, ... OR(?) .47µF to extend reset time\n* input capacitance of 47µF + .1µF\n	really that much needed; 10µF not enough?\n	no external chip/motherboard powered"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 213.36 40.386 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
